{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/git-cheatsheet","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"9b3b8c32-70c0-5e01-ba70-a615b07b0eeb","html":"<p>While writing software, Version Control is very important. Every software developer must learn to use version control. Git has become the default version control tool, and a software developer can’t skip learning this tool.  </p>\n<p>This article is intended for readers who have just started using git. Hopefully this helps them in making the git journey more fun.</p>\n<p>Mentioning common git commands and aliases below.</p>\n<h2 id=\"common-git-commands\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#common-git-commands\" aria-label=\"common git commands permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Common Git Commands</h2>\n<h3 id=\"clone-a-repository\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#clone-a-repository\" aria-label=\"clone a repository permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Clone a repository</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\">git clone &lt;repository_name&gt; &lt;destination_folder&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<p>if <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;destination_folder&gt;</code> is not given git creates a new folder with the name of the repo.</p>\n<p>The following clones the <a href=\"https://github.com/facebook/react\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">official React repo</a>, into the a new folder react into your local machine.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prd-hc-oj-public-1/public/users/73794b05-fe63-4188-81cd-b6fd35c7aa4e/images/5Sex4ntFGqjYT1NPTPyXuzQaZDJbdtqv\" alt=\"git-clone\"></p>\n<p>And the following clone the React repo, in the folder called <code class=\"language-text\">my-react</code>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prd-hc-oj-public-1/public/users/73794b05-fe63-4188-81cd-b6fd35c7aa4e/images/fcom9lpIihWQGhqpQKnWj1M7xl2myG7s\" alt=\"git-clone\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"to-start-a-new-git-tracked-repo\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#to-start-a-new-git-tracked-repo\" aria-label=\"to start a new git tracked repo permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>To start a new git tracked repo</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\">mkdir new-project\n﻿\ngit init     # Makes the current directory a git tracked repo\n\n# Add files to the new-project\n# Its a good idea to add a &#39;README.md&#39; file and a &#39;.gitignore&#39; file and then make your first commit.\n﻿\n# Adds all the files in the current directory\ngit add .\n﻿\n# Make your first commit and give a meaningful message\ngit commit -m &quot;Add README and gitignore&quot;</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"configure-your-git-installation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#configure-your-git-installation\" aria-label=\"configure your git installation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Configure your git installation</h3>\n<p>Add your username and email to git config so that git can add them in each that you make.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\">git config --global user.name &quot;your_username&quot;\ngit config --global user.email your_email@example.com</code></pre></div>\n<p>Git shows the user details in logs etc.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prd-hc-oj-public-1/public/users/73794b05-fe63-4188-81cd-b6fd35c7aa4e/images/e93yMczUbrfxO8FpDy3lrCB10fU9n7Q8\" alt=\"git log\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"making-changes-in-your-local-and-push-it-to-remote-repo\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#making-changes-in-your-local-and-push-it-to-remote-repo\" aria-label=\"making changes in your local and push it to remote repo permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Making changes in your local and push it to remote repo</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\"># Make changes in the files\n\n# Check which files has changes\ngit status</code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"https://s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prd-hc-oj-public-1/public/users/73794b05-fe63-4188-81cd-b6fd35c7aa4e/images/j4KZpA218BYXb88M4tJohFa1UNgZk4SN\" alt=\"git status\"></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\"># Add changes to the staging area\ngit add &lt;file1&gt; &lt;file2&gt;\n\n# Or to add all changes\ngit add .\n\n# Files in the staging area are shown in green colour</code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"https://s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prd-hc-oj-public-1/public/users/73794b05-fe63-4188-81cd-b6fd35c7aa4e/images/Z1AqY60Cyj9ENZgXhxfn1DwaCZy1ukVu\" alt=\"git status\"></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\"> # Commit the changes in the staging area\ngit commit -m &quot;A meaningful commit message&quot;\n\n# push the changes in the remote repo\ngit push origin &lt;current_branch_name&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"switch-between-branches\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#switch-between-branches\" aria-label=\"switch between branches permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Switch between branches</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\">git checkout &lt;branch&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"merge-your-branch-in-master\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#merge-your-branch-in-master\" aria-label=\"merge your branch in master permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Merge your branch in master</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\"># Switch to master branch\ngit checkout master\n﻿\ngit merge &lt;your_branch&gt;\n\n# Might have conflicts. Resolve conflicts and then continue merging.\n\n# Check logs to see if the changes have been incorporated\ngit log\n\n# If everything looks fine, push to remote master\ngit push origin master</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"determine-what-changes-you-have-made\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#determine-what-changes-you-have-made\" aria-label=\"determine what changes you have made permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Determine what changes you have made</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\">git diff &lt;filename&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"https://s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/prd-hc-oj-public-1/public/users/73794b05-fe63-4188-81cd-b6fd35c7aa4e/images/9UU5KQKtF8BQrQ7hP31BVFBU6FzJMcpY\" alt=\"git diff\"></p>\n<p>Additions and deletions are shown by + and - signs, and can be color-coded depending on the shell you use.</p>\n<h2 id=\"useful-aliases\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#useful-aliases\" aria-label=\"useful aliases permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Useful Aliases</h2>\n<p>Git is a very useful tool, something that developers use multiple times in a\nday. Typing git commands can be eased by using aliases to most common commands\nlike <code class=\"language-text\">git status</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">git push</code>.</p>\n<p>Mentioning few useful aliases below. Include them in your <code class=\"language-text\">~/.bashrc</code> file. Your\nconfiguration file may vary depending on your operating system and shell. If you\nare using Ubuntu or Mac OS X, <code class=\"language-text\">~/.bashrc</code> is the file you need. If the file\ndoesn’t exist, create the file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\">g=git\n\n# Use: ga README.md .gitignore\nga=&#39;git add&#39;\n\n# To add deleted files also\ngaa=&#39;git add --all&#39;\n\n# Use: gcmsg &quot;Meaningful commit message&quot;\ngcmsg=&#39;git commit -m&#39;\n\n# To switch to another branch\n# Use: gco master\ngco=&#39;git checkout&#39;\n\n# Use: gd &lt;filename&gt;\ngd=&#39;git diff&#39;\n\n# Get the list of branches, and you current branch\ngb=&#39;git branch&#39;\n\n# Use: gc -m &quot;A meaningful message&quot;\ngc=&#39;git commit -v&#39;</code></pre></div>\n<p>Function to get the current branch name.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\">function git_current_branch() {  \n    local ref  \n    ref=$(command git symbolic-ref --quiet HEAD 2&gt; /dev/null)  \n    local ret=$?  \n    if [[ $ret != 0 ]]; then \n        [[ $ret == 128 ]] &amp;&amp; return  # no git repo.  \n        ref=$(command git rev-parse --short HEAD 2&gt; /dev/null) || return  \n    fi\n    echo ${ref#refs/heads/}\n}</code></pre></div>\n<p>Aliases for <code class=\"language-text\">git push</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">git pull</code>. These save typing a lot of characters, and possible typos. Very useful!</p>\n<p>Pull your current branch to remote.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\"># Use:\n# git checkout &lt;your_branch&gt;\n# ggpull  # Get the latest changes from remote\n\nggpull=&#39;git pull origin $(git_current_branch)&#39;</code></pre></div>\n<p>Push your current branch to remote. A new branch in remote is created, if already not present.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\"># Use: After making commits to your current branch\n# ggpush\n\nggpush=&#39;git push origin $(git_current_branch)&#39;</code></pre></div>\n<p>Hope this cheatsheet makes your git journey easier.</p>\n<p>Happy coding! 😊</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/git-cheatsheet","tagSlugs":["/tag/git/","/tag/cheatsheet/","/tag/advanced/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2021-01-01","description":"Tips to enhance your Git workflow.","tags":["git","cheatsheet","advanced"],"title":"Git Cheatsheet","socialImage":"/media/gutenberg.jpg"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/git-cheatsheet"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","3942705351","401334301"]}